#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &digikam; <emphasis>Add Border</emphasis> is a tool to frame an image with decorative borders."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keeping the viewer's interest within the confines of the edges of a photograph is not a simple task. One of the simplest ways to hold the attention on an image is to incorporate a decorative frame around an image. It acts as a kind of psychological barrier to the straying eye. The <menuchoice><guimenu>Image</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Add Border</guimenuitem></menuchoice> Image Editor menu can be used for that."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Add-border tool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "Four options give you control over the decorative frame rendering:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Type</guilabel>: this option specifies the decorative frame style to apply around the image. <guilabel>Solid</guilabel> style just surrounds the image with a colored line, <guilabel>Niepce</guilabel> style surrounds the image with a fine line and a large border (ideal for black and white images), <guilabel>Beveled</guilabel> style adds a neat dimension to your image (ideal to create a button effect), and <guilabel>Decorative</guilabel> style adds an ornamental border using patterns."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Width</guilabel>: this option specifies the border width in percents of image size. The border is added around the image. The width range is limited between 1% and 50%."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>First</guilabel>: this option specifies the first color to use with the current border type."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Second</guilabel>: this option specifies the second color to use with the current border type."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click on the <guilabel>OK</guilabel> button to apply the border around the current image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: editor-decorate-border.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "The border decorated target image will be bigger than the original, but it will retain the same aspect ratio. This is important for printing images, especially if you have used the Aspect Ratio Crop tool before."
msgstr ""

